						<table width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td id="projectmodleftside"></td> 
						<td class="projectboxcontent" width="978" valign="top"><div class="globalheader">Recent Blog Posts <span class="pagelinks">[<a href="/The_Path/blog/">read blog</a>]</div><div class="projectboxcontent" align="left"><div class="projectboxcontent" style="padding-left:10px;height:600px; overflow:auto;""><b>Wevolt: Trinity</b><div style="color:#;font-size:px;">posted: 2010-09-29 00:00:00</div><div style="color:#;font-size:px;border-bottom:dashed # 1px; padding-top:5px;padding-bottom:5px;">So, I did the image attached to this blog post on a whim when I started doing The Path pages digitally. I needed to practice my tablet-fu, and what better way than to draw a picture of Chance out for a drink with <a href="../../Phinmagic/">Phineus Beam</a>&nbsp;and <a href="../../Locus/">Locus</a>? None that I could think of. I've gotten better in the few months since I did this...but this sort of got me thinking about getting Barry Linck(Phineus creator) and Adam Black(Locus creator) to agree to do a crossover. In fact, I started an ill-fated crossover with Barry a few years ago, but life got in the way and the project was put on the back burner.&nbsp;</p>

<p>Anyway, long story short, I pitched a crossover idea to these two VERY talented guys (who i also happen to be a fan of, it boggles my mind that they consider me a peer), who liked it, and <a href="../../Wevolt_Trinity/">Wevolt: Trinity</a> was born!</p>

<p>"Trinity" is going to be a group effort with all three of us taking on story and art chores. Starting this Friday (Oct 1st), Trinity will update with three variant covers: the first by Barry Linck, the second by yours truly, and the third by Adam Black. Then, on Monday, the first of three prologues go up. The prologues will explain WHY Phineus, Locus, and Chance wind up together. Then on Halloween, the "main" comic will begin updating with...some sort of fanfare. I'm sure we'll be hyping it big time for the next month. In the month following the big "debut", there will be a special book put together with all the prologue stories and some cool extras, too!</p>

<p>But, seriously. Staple your socks on, and wear a helmet. This is going to be fucking EPIC!</div><b>"What I Do Best" The Path-inspired Music Download!</b><div style="color:#;font-size:px;">posted: 2010-09-16 00:00:00</div><div style="color:#;font-size:px;border-bottom:dashed # 1px; padding-top:5px;padding-bottom:5px;"><a href="http://www.mediafire.com/?9jbqy2654qatx84"></a></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>So, what we have here is a nice little "off day" treat! Girl Named Sam (who wrote the song "Legendary" in the last blog post about The Path) has sent me another song called "What I Do Best". The song is pretty much about Chance lamenting how he couldn't save Kat and lost her. It's pretty awesome, you should check it out!</p>

<p>You can find more of Girl Named Sam's music here: http://www.facebook.com/girlnamedsammusic</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

